What is USB HID Proxy Mode?
•	HID (Human Interface Device) Proxy mode makes PiKVM present itself to Windows only as a standard USB keyboard and mouse.
•	It prevents detection as a custom KVM device, reducing the chance of driver blocks or USB policy restrictions.
1. Start HID (Keyboard & Mouse) Emulation


sudo kvmd-otg start
Then verify HID devices:


ls -l /dev/hidg*
If you see /dev/hidg0, /dev/hidg1, etc., HID is active.
________________________________________
2. Enable HID on Boot (Persistent Setting)
If you want HID to start automatically:


sudo systemctl enable --now kvmd
________________________________________
3. Restart the Pi-KVM Service


sudo systemctl restart kvmd
________________________________________
4. Check KVMD Logs for Errors
If HID still isn’t working, check:


journalctl -u kvmd --no-pager --no-full | tail -20

